Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Shanghai, March 4 (XINHUA) -- China Eastern Airlines 
will this year buy four airbuses from the Airbus Industrie of 
Europe, according to official sources. 
  China Northern Airlines and Northwestern Airlines have also 
ordered five airbuses from the company, according to a press 
conference held here Tuesday [2 March] by the company. 
  Officials of the company in charge of China affairs said 
that 
the company plans to set up a training center in Beijing, to 
train professional pilots for China. 
  The company and the China aviation suppliers corporation 
several days ago signed a co-operative pact under which some 
departments of the China aviation industry will produce spare 
parts for the company, official sources said. 

